## How It Works

```
"3 + 4 * 2"
     │
     ▼
  Lexer  →  [Number(3), Plus, Number(4), Star, Number(2)]
     │
     ▼
  Parser (recursive descent)
     │
     parse_expr
     ├── parse_term → parse_factor → parse_base → 3.0
     ├── sees Plus, advances
     └── parse_term
         ├── parse_factor → parse_base → 4.0
         ├── sees Star, advances
         └── parse_factor → parse_base → 2.0   →  4 * 2 = 8.0
     →  3 + 8 = 11.0
```

### Operator Precedence (lowest → highest)

| Level | Operators | Associativity |
|-------|-----------|---------------|
| 1 | `+` `-` | Left |
| 2 | `*` `/` `%` | Left |
| 3 | `^` | **Right** |
| 4 | Unary `-` `+` | Right |
| 5 | `( )` literals | — |

