## How It Works

### Core Algorithm (Treiber Stack)

```
Push:                          Pop:
  1. Allocate new node           1. Read head
  2. Read current head           2. If null → return None
  3. Set node.next = head        3. Read head.next
  4. CAS(head, old, new)         4. CAS(head, old, head.next)
  5. Retry on failure            5. Return data; retire old node
```

### Memory Ordering Rationale

| Operation | Ordering | Reason |
|-----------|----------|--------|
| `push` store | `Release` | Publishes node data before pointer |
| `pop` load | `Acquire` | Sees all writes before the Release |
| `CAS` success | `Release`/`Acquire` | Synchronizes producer-consumer |
| Counter updates | `Acquire`/`Release` | Guards the critical section |

### Memory Reclamation Strategy

```
pop() increments active_readers
  → retires freed node to lock-free list
pop() decrements active_readers
  → last reader drains retired list safely
```

### Key Safety Guarantees

- **No data races**: All shared state accessed through atomics
- **No use-after-free**: Retired nodes only freed when `active_readers == 0`  
- **Proper destruction**: `Drop` impl calls `pop()` to run `T`'s destructors
- **ABA mitigation**: Epoch-based reclamation prevents reuse during active reads

# B-Tree Implementation in Rust

## Overview

This implementation provides a complete B-tree with insertion, deletion, search, and traversal operations. A B-tree of order `t` (minimum degree) maintains the invariant that every non-root node has at least `t-1` keys and at most `2t-1` keys.

```rust
use std::fmt::Debug;

/// B-Tree with minimum degree `t`
/// - Every non-root node has at least t-1 keys
/// - Every node has at most 2t-1 keys
/// - Root has at least 1 key (unless tree is empty)
pub struct BTree<K: Ord + Clone + Debug, V: Clone + Debug> {
    root: Option<Box<Node<K, V>>>,
    t: usize, // minimum degree
    len: usize,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
struct Node<K: Ord + Clone + Debug, V: Clone + Debug> {
    keys: Vec<K>,
    values: Vec<V>,
    children: Vec<Box<Node<K, V>>>,
    is_leaf: bool,
}

impl<K: Ord + Clone + Debug, V: Clone + Debug> Node<K, V> {
    fn new(is_leaf: bool) -> Self {
        Node {
            keys: Vec::new(),
            values: Vec::new(),
            children: Vec::new(),
            is_leaf,
        }
    }

    fn is_full(&self, t: usize) -> bool {
        self.keys.len() == 2 * t - 1
    }

    /// Search for a key in the subtree rooted at this node.
    /// Returns Some(&value) if found, None otherwise.
    fn search(&self, key: &K) -> Option<&V> {
        let idx = self.keys.partition_point(|k| k < key);

        if idx < self.keys.len() && &self.keys[idx] == key {
            return Some(&self.values[idx]);
        }

        if self.is_leaf {
            None
        } else {
            self.children[idx].search(key)
        }
    }

    /// Mutable search — returns Some(&mut value) if found.
    fn search_mut(&mut self, key: &K) -> Option<&mut V> {
        let idx = self.keys.partition_point(|k| k < key);

        if idx < self.keys.len() && &self.keys[idx] == key {
            return Some(&mut self.values[idx]);
        }

        if self.is_leaf {
            None
        } else {
            self.children[idx].search_mut(key)
        }
    }

    /// Split the `i`-th child of this node (which must be full).
    /// After splitting, the median key moves up to this node.
    fn split_child(&mut self, i: usize, t: usize) {
        let mid = t - 1; // index of median in the full child

        // We'll take the right half out of children[i]
        let (median_key, median_val, right_child) = {
            let left = &mut self.children[i];

            let right_keys = left.keys.split_off(mid + 1);
            let right_values = left.values.split_off(mid + 1);
            let median_key = left.keys.pop().unwrap();
            let median_val = left.values.pop().unwrap();

            let right_children = if left.is_leaf {
                Vec::new()
            } else {
                left.children.split_off(mid + 1)
            };

            let right_node = Node {
                keys: right_keys,
                values: right_values,
                children: right_children,
                is_leaf: left.is_leaf,
            };

            (median_key, median_val, Box::new(right_node))
        };

        // Insert median into this node
        self.keys.insert(i, median_key);
        self.values.insert(i, median_val);
        self.children.insert(i + 1, right_child);
    }

    /// Insert into a non-full node (split children proactively on the way down).
    fn insert_non_full(&mut self, key: K, value: V, t: usize) {
        let mut idx = self.keys.partition_point(|k| k < &key);

        // Key already exists — update value
        if idx < self.keys.len() && self.keys[idx] == key {
            self.values[idx] = value;
            return;
        }

        if self.is_leaf {
            self.keys.insert(idx, key);
            self.values.insert(idx, value);
        } else {
            if self.children[idx].is_full(t) {
                self.split_child(idx, t);
                // After split, the median moved up; decide which half to go into
                if self.keys[idx] < key {
                    idx += 1;
                } else if self.keys[idx] == key {
                    self.values[idx] = value;
                    return;
                }
            }
            self.children[idx].insert_non_full(key, value, t);
        }
    }

    // ------------------------------------------------------------------ //
    //  Deletion helpers
    // ------------------------------------------------------------------ //

    /// Find predecessor (largest key in left subtree of index `idx`).
    fn predecessor(&self, idx: usize) -> (K, V) {
        let mut cur = &self.children[idx];
        while !cur.is_leaf {
            cur = cur.children.last().unwrap();
        }
        let last = cur.keys.len() - 1;
        (cur.keys[last].clone(), cur.values[last].clone())
    }

    /// Find successor (smallest key in right subtree of index `idx`).
    fn successor(&self, idx: usize) -> (K, V) {
        let mut cur = &self.children[idx + 1];
        while !cur.is_leaf {
            cur = cur.children.first().unwrap();
        }
        (cur.keys[0].clone(), cur.values[0].clone())
    }

    /// Merge children[idx] and children[idx+1] around keys[idx].
    /// The merged node replaces children[idx]; children[idx+1] is removed.
    fn merge_children(&mut self, idx: usize) {
        let sep_key = self.keys.remove(idx);
        let sep_val = self.values.remove(idx);
        let right = self.children.remove(idx + 1);
        let left = &mut self.children[idx];

        left.keys.push(sep_key);
        left.values.push(sep_val);
        left.keys.extend(right.keys);
        left.values.extend(right.values);
        left.children.extend(right.children);
    }

    /// Borrow a key from children[idx-1] (left sibling) for children[idx].
    fn borrow_from_left(&mut self, idx: usize) {
        let sep_key = self.keys[idx - 1].clone();
        let sep_val = self.values[idx - 1].clone();

        let (sibling_key, sibling_val, sibling_child) = {
            let sibling = &mut self.children[idx - 1];
            let k = sibling.keys.pop().unwrap();
            let v = sibling.values.pop().unwrap();
            let c = if sibling.is_leaf {
                None
            } else {
                Some(sibling.children.pop().unwrap())
            };
            (k, v, c)
        };

        self.keys[idx - 1] = sibling_key;
        self.values[idx - 1] = sibling_val;

        let child = &mut self.children[idx];
        child.keys.insert(0, sep_key);
        child.values.insert(0, sep_val);
        if let Some(c) = sibling_child {
            child.children.insert(0, c);
        }
    }

    /// Borrow a key from children[idx+1] (right sibling) for children[idx].
    fn borrow_from_right(&mut self, idx: usize) {
        let sep_key = self.keys[idx].clone();
        let sep_val = self.values[idx].clone();

        let (sibling_key, sibling_val, sibling_child) = {
            let sibling = &mut self.children[idx + 1];
            let k = sibling.keys.remove(0);
            let v = sibling.values.remove(0);
            let c = if sibling.is_leaf {
                None
            } else {
                Some(sibling.children.remove(0))
            };
            (k, v, c)
        };

        self.keys[idx] = sibling_key;
        self.values[idx] = sibling_val;

        let child = &mut self.children[idx];
        child.keys.push(sep_key);
        child.values.push(sep_val);
        if let Some(c) = sibling_child {
            child.children.push(c);
        }
    }

    /// Ensure children[idx] has at least `t` keys before descending.
    /// Returns the (possibly adjusted) index to descend into after fixup.
    fn fix_child(&mut self, idx: usize, t: usize) -> usize {
        if self.children[idx].keys.len() >= t {
            return idx; // already has enough keys
        }

        let has_left = idx > 0;
        let has_right = idx + 1 < self.children.len();

        if has_left && self.children[idx - 1].keys.len() >= t {
            self.borrow_from_left(idx);
            idx
        } else if has_right && self.children[idx + 1].keys.len() >= t {
            self.borrow_from_right(idx);
            idx
        } else if has_left {
            self.merge_children(idx - 1);
            idx - 1 // merged into left sibling
        } else {
            self.merge_children(idx);
            idx // merged left child with right sibling
        }
    }

    /// Delete a key from the subtree rooted here.
    /// Returns Some(value) if the key was found and removed.
    fn delete(&mut self, key: &K, t: usize) -> Option<V> {
        let idx = self.keys.partition_point(|k| k < key);
        let found = idx < self.keys.len() && &self.keys[idx] == key;

        if self.is_leaf {
            if found {
                self.keys.remove(idx);
                return Some(self.values.remove(idx));
            }
            return None;
        }

        if found {
            // Case A: key is in this internal node
            let left_len = self.children[idx].keys.len();
            let right_len = self.children[idx + 1].keys.len();

            if left_len >= t {
                // Replace with predecessor, then delete predecessor
                let (pred_k, pred_v) = self.predecessor(idx);
                self.keys[idx] = pred_k.clone();
                let old_val = std::mem::replace(&mut self.values[idx], pred_v);
                self.children[idx].delete(&pred_k, t);
                return Some(old_val);
            } else if right_len >= t {
                // Replace with successor, then delete successor
                let (succ_k, succ_v) = self.successor(idx);
                self.keys[idx] = succ_k.clone();
                let old_val = std::mem::replace(&mut self.values[idx], succ_v);
                self.children[idx + 1].delete(&succ_k, t);
                return Some(old_val);
            } else {
                // Both children have t-1 keys → merge them
                self.merge_children(idx);
                return self.children[idx].delete(key, t);
            }
        }

        // Case B: key is not in this node → descend
        let child_idx = self.fix_child(idx, t);
        self.children[child_idx].delete(key, t)
    }

    /// In-order traversal — calls `f` with (key, value) pairs in sorted order.
    fn traverse<F: FnMut(&K, &V)>(&self, f: &mut F) {
        for i in 0..self.keys.len() {
            if !self.is_leaf {
                self.children[i].traverse(f);
            }
            f(&self.keys[i], &self.values[i]);
        }
        if !self.is_leaf {
            self.children[self.keys.len()].traverse(f);
        }
    }

    /// Compute the height of the subtree (leaves are height 1).
    fn height(&self) -> usize {
        if self.is_leaf {
            1
        } else {
            1 + self.children[0].height()
        }
    }

    /// Validate B-tree invariants (for testing).
    fn validate(&self, t: usize, is_root: bool) -> Result<(K, K), String> {
        let n = self.keys.len();

        if !is_root && n < t - 1 {
            return Err(format!("Node has too few keys: {} < {}", n, t - 1));
        }
        if n > 2 * t - 1 {
            return Err(format!("Node has too many keys: {} > {}", n, 2 * t - 1));
        }
        if !self.is_leaf && self.children.len() != n + 1 {
            return Err(format!(
                "Internal node has {} keys but {} children",
                n,
                self.children.len()
            ));
        }
        for i in 1..n {
            if self.keys[i - 1] >= self.keys[i] {
                return Err(format!("Keys not sorted at index {}", i));
            }
        }

        if self.is_leaf {
            return Ok((self.keys[0].clone(), self.keys[n - 1].clone()));
        }

        // Validate children and check ordering
        let mut child_ranges = Vec::new();
        for child in &self.children {
            child_ranges.push(child.validate(t, false)?);
        }

        for i in 0..n {
            if child_ranges[i].1 >= self.keys[i] {
                return Err(format!(
                    "Left child max {:?} >= separator {:?}",
                    child_ranges[i].1, self.keys[i]
                ));
            }
            if child_ranges[i + 1].0 <= self.keys[i] {
                return Err(format!(
                    "Right child min {:?} <= separator {:?}",
                    child_ranges[i + 1].0, self.keys[i]
                ));
            }
        }

        Ok((child_ranges[0].0.clone(), child_ranges[n].1.clone()))
    }
}

// ------------------------------------------------------------------ //
//  BTree public API
// ------------------------------------------------------------------ //

impl<K: Ord + Clone + Debug, V: Clone + Debug> BTree<K, V> {
    /// Create a new B-tree with minimum degree `t` (must be ≥ 2).
    pub fn new(t: usize) -> Self {
        assert!(t >= 2, "Minimum degree t must be >= 2");
        BTree {
            root: None,
            t,
            len: 0,
        }
    }

    /// Returns the number of key-value pairs in the tree.
    pub fn len(&self) -> usize {
        self.len
    }

    /// Returns true if the tree contains no keys.
    pub fn is_empty(&self) -> bool {
        self.len == 0
    }

    /// Search for a key, returning a reference to the associated value.
    pub fn get(&self, key: &K) -> Option<&V> {
        self.root.as_ref()?.search(key)
    }

    /// Search for a key, returning a mutable reference to the associated value.
    pub fn get_mut(&mut self, key: &K) -> Option<&mut V> {
        self.root.as_mut()?.search_mut(key)
    }

    /// Returns true if the tree contains the given key.
    pub fn contains_key(&self, key: &K) -> bool {
        self.get(key).is_some()
    }

    /// Insert a key-value pair. If the key already exists, its value is updated
    /// and the old value is returned; otherwise None is returned.
    pub fn insert(&mut self, key: K, value: V) -> Option<V> {
        let already_present = self.contains_key(&key);

        if self.root.is_none() {
            let mut root = Box::new(Node::new(true));
            root.keys.push(key);
            root.values.push(value);
            self.root = Some(root);
            self.len += 1;
            return None;
        }

        // If root is full, split it first
        if self.root.as_ref().unwrap().is_full(self.t) {
            let old_root = self.root.take().unwrap();
            let mut new_root = Box::new(Node::new(false));
            new_root.children.push(old_root);
            new_root.split_child(0, self.t);
            self.root = Some(new_root);
        }

        // Capture old value before overwriting (for return)
        let old_val = if already_present {
            self.get(&key).cloned().map(|v| {
                // We'll return this after insertion overwrites it
                v
            })
        } else {
            None
        };

        self.root
            .as_mut()
            .unwrap()
            .insert_non_full(key, value, self.t);

        if !already_present {
            self.len += 1;
        }

        old_val
    }

    /// Remove a key from the tree, returning its value if present.
    pub fn remove(&mut self, key: &K) -> Option<V> {
        let root = self.root.as_mut()?;
        let result = root.delete(key, self.t);

        if result.is_some() {
            self.len -= 1;
            // If the root is now empty (all keys merged into a child), shrink the tree
            if self.root.as_ref().unwrap().keys.is_empty() {
                self.root = if self.root.as_ref().unwrap().is_leaf {
                    None
                } else {
                    Some(self.root.as_mut().unwrap().children.remove(0))
                };
            }
        }

        result
    }

    /// Perform an in-order traversal, calling `f` with each (key, value) pair.
    pub fn traverse<F: FnMut(&K, &V)>(&self, mut f: F) {
        if let Some(root) = &self.root {
            root.traverse(&mut f);
        }
    }

    /// Collect all (key, value) pairs in sorted order.
    pub fn to_vec(&self) -> Vec<(K, V)> {
        let mut result = Vec::with_capacity(self.len);
        self.traverse(|k, v| result.push((k.clone(), v.clone())));
        result
    }

    /// Return the height of the tree (0 if empty).
    pub fn height(&self) -> usize {
        self.root.as_ref().map_or(0, |r| r.height())
    }

    /// Validate all B-tree invariants. Returns Ok(()) or an error message.
    pub fn validate(&self) -> Result<(), String> {
        match &self.root {
            None => Ok(()),
            Some(root) => {
                if root.keys.is_empty() {
                    return Ok(()); // empty root
                }
                root.validate(self.t, true).map(|_| ())
            }
        }
    }
}

// ------------------------------------------------------------------ //
//  Display
// ------------------------------------------------------------------ //

impl<K: Ord + Clone + Debug, V: Clone + Debug> std::fmt::Display for BTree<K, V> {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut std::fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> std::fmt::Result {
        fn fmt_node<K: Ord + Clone + Debug, V: Clone + Debug>(
            node: &Node<K, V>,
            f: &mut std::fmt::Formatter<'_>,
            depth: usize,
        ) -> std::fmt::Result {
            let indent = "  ".repeat(depth);
            writeln!(f, "{}Keys: {:?}", indent, node.keys)?;
            if !node.is_leaf {
                for child in &node.children {
                    fmt_node(child, f, depth + 1)?;
                }
            }
            Ok(())
        }

        match &self.root {
            None => writeln!(f, "(empty)"),
            Some(root) => fmt_node(root, f, 0),
        }
    }
}

