## How It Works

### Core Data Structure

```
Every node is wrapped in Arc<Tree> so multiple
versions can SHARE unchanged subtrees cheaply:

    v1 (insert A)        v2 (insert B)
         R                    R'
        / \                  / \
       A   …               B   …
            ↘               ↗
             shared subtree
```

### Key Design Decisions

| Aspect | Choice | Reason |
|--------|--------|--------|
| Sharing | `Arc<Tree>` | Thread-safe reference counting for structural sharing |
| Invariant repair | Okasaki's 4-case `balance` | Simple, purely functional |
| Immutability | All functions return new `Arc`s | Old versions never mutated |
| Root color | Forced black after every insert | Maintains invariant #1 |

### Red-Black Invariants

1. **Root is black** — enforced in `PersistentMap::insert`
2. **No red-red** — caught and fixed by `balance` during insertion
3. **Equal black-height on all paths** — maintained by `balance`; verified by `check_invariants`

### Complexity

| Operation | Time | New nodes allocated |
|-----------|------|---------------------|
| `insert`  | O(log n) | O(log n) |
| `get`     | O(log n) | 0 |
| `to_sorted_vec` | O(n) | 0 |

# Tri-Color Garbage Collector in Rust

## Overview

The tri-color marking algorithm uses three sets:
- **White**: Not yet visited (candidates for collection)
- **Gray**: Discovered but children not yet processed
- **Black**: Fully processed (reachable, children also reachable)

```rust
use std::collections::{HashMap, HashSet, VecDeque};
use std::fmt;

// ============================================================
// Core Types
// ============================================================

/// Unique identifier for a heap object
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
pub struct ObjectId(usize);

impl fmt::Display for ObjectId {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        write!(f, "Obj({})", self.0)
    }
}

/// Color of an object in the tri-color marking scheme
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub enum Color {
    /// Not yet visited; candidate for collection
    White,
    /// Discovered but children not yet fully processed
    Gray,
    /// Fully processed; reachable
    Black,
}

impl fmt::Display for Color {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        match self {
            Color::White => write!(f, "White"),
            Color::Gray => write!(f, "Gray"),
            Color::Black => write!(f, "Black"),
        }
    }
}

/// Value stored inside a heap object
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub enum Value {
    Integer(i64),
    Float(f64),
    Boolean(bool),
    String(String),
    Null,
    /// Reference to another heap object
    Reference(ObjectId),
    /// Array of values (may contain references)
    Array(Vec<Value>),
}

impl fmt::Display for Value {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        match self {
            Value::Integer(n) => write!(f, "{}", n),
            Value::Float(n) => write!(f, "{}", n),
            Value::Boolean(b) => write!(f, "{}", b),
            Value::String(s) => write!(f, "\"{}\"", s),
            Value::Null => write!(f, "null"),
            Value::Reference(id) => write!(f, "ref({})", id),
            Value::Array(arr) => {
                write!(f, "[")?;
                for (i, v) in arr.iter().enumerate() {
                    if i > 0 {
                        write!(f, ", ")?;
                    }
                    write!(f, "{}", v)?;
                }
                write!(f, "]")
            }
        }
    }
}

impl Value {
    /// Extract all ObjectIds referenced by this value
    pub fn references(&self) -> Vec<ObjectId> {
        match self {
            Value::Reference(id) => vec![*id],
            Value::Array(arr) => arr.iter().flat_map(|v| v.references()).collect(),
            _ => vec![],
        }
    }
}

/// A single object on the managed heap
#[derive(Debug)]
pub struct HeapObject {
    pub id: ObjectId,
    pub color: Color,
    /// Named fields
    pub fields: HashMap<String, Value>,
}

impl HeapObject {
    pub fn new(id: ObjectId) -> Self {
        Self {
            id,
            color: Color::White,
            fields: HashMap::new(),
        }
    }

    /// Collect all ObjectIds referenced by any field
    pub fn references(&self) -> Vec<ObjectId> {
        self.fields.values().flat_map(|v| v.references()).collect()
    }

    pub fn set_field(&mut self, key: impl Into<String>, value: Value) {
        self.fields.insert(key.into(), value);
    }
}

impl fmt::Display for HeapObject {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        write!(f, "[{} color={} fields={{", self.id, self.color)?;
        for (i, (k, v)) in self.fields.iter().enumerate() {
            if i > 0 {
                write!(f, ", ")?;
            }
            write!(f, "{}={}", k, v)?;
        }
        write!(f, "}}]")
    }
}

// ============================================================
// GC Statistics
// ============================================================

#[derive(Debug, Default, Clone)]
pub struct GcStats {
    pub collections_run: usize,
    pub objects_allocated: usize,
    pub objects_collected: usize,
    pub objects_survived: usize,
}

impl fmt::Display for GcStats {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        write!(
            f,
            "GcStats {{ runs={}, allocated={}, collected={}, survived={} }}",
            self.collections_run,
            self.objects_allocated,
            self.objects_collected,
            self.objects_survived
        )
    }
}

// ============================================================
// Write Barrier
// ============================================================

/// Events generated by the write barrier during incremental GC
#[derive(Debug)]
pub enum WriteBarrierEvent {
    /// A black object now points to a white object — re-shade the white object gray
    ReshadeGray(ObjectId),
}

// ============================================================
// Tri-Color Garbage Collector
// ============================================================

pub struct TriColorGc {
    /// All live heap objects
    heap: HashMap<ObjectId, HeapObject>,
    /// Root set (direct GC roots, e.g. stack variables, globals)
    roots: HashSet<ObjectId>,
    /// Next object id counter
    next_id: usize,
    /// Statistics
    pub stats: GcStats,
    /// Whether an incremental GC cycle is in progress
    incremental_active: bool,
    /// Gray worklist for incremental marking
    gray_worklist: VecDeque<ObjectId>,
}

impl TriColorGc {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        Self {
            heap: HashMap::new(),
            roots: HashSet::new(),
            next_id: 0,
            stats: GcStats::default(),
            incremental_active: false,
            gray_worklist: VecDeque::new(),
        }
    }

    // ----------------------------------------------------------
    // Allocation
    // ----------------------------------------------------------

    /// Allocate a new object and return its id
    pub fn allocate(&mut self) -> ObjectId {
        let id = ObjectId(self.next_id);
        self.next_id += 1;
        let obj = HeapObject::new(id);
        self.heap.insert(id, obj);
        self.stats.objects_allocated += 1;

        // During incremental GC, new objects are born black to avoid
        // them being collected before they are fully initialized.
        if self.incremental_active {
            self.heap.get_mut(&id).unwrap().color = Color::Black;
        }

        id
    }

    /// Allocate an object and add it to the root set
    pub fn allocate_root(&mut self) -> ObjectId {
        let id = self.allocate();
        self.roots.insert(id);
        id
    }

    // ----------------------------------------------------------
    // Root management
    // ----------------------------------------------------------

    pub fn add_root(&mut self, id: ObjectId) {
        self.roots.insert(id);
    }

    pub fn remove_root(&mut self, id: ObjectId) {
        self.roots.remove(&id);
    }

    // ----------------------------------------------------------
    // Field mutation (with write barrier)
    // ----------------------------------------------------------

    /// Set a field on an object. Applies the write barrier when an
    /// incremental cycle is active (Dijkstra/snapshot-at-the-beginning
    /// style: keep the invariant that no black object points to white).
    pub fn set_field(
        &mut self,
        obj_id: ObjectId,
        field: impl Into<String>,
        value: Value,
    ) -> Option<WriteBarrierEvent> {
        let field = field.into();

        // Check write barrier *before* mutation
        let event = if self.incremental_active {
            self.write_barrier(obj_id, &value)
        } else {
            None
        };

        if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get_mut(&obj_id) {
            obj.set_field(field, value);
        }

        // Apply barrier effect
        if let Some(WriteBarrierEvent::ReshadeGray(target)) = &event {
            if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get_mut(target) {
                if obj.color == Color::White {
                    obj.color = Color::Gray;
                    self.gray_worklist.push_back(*target);
                }
            }
        }

        event
    }

    /// Dijkstra write barrier: if we write a reference into a black object,
    /// the target must be at least gray.
    fn write_barrier(&self, src_id: ObjectId, new_value: &Value) -> Option<WriteBarrierEvent> {
        let src_color = self.heap.get(&src_id)?.color;
        if src_color == Color::Black {
            // Find all references in the new value
            for target_id in new_value.references() {
                if let Some(target) = self.heap.get(&target_id) {
                    if target.color == Color::White {
                        return Some(WriteBarrierEvent::ReshadeGray(target_id));
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        None
    }

    // ----------------------------------------------------------
    // Stop-the-world collection
    // ----------------------------------------------------------

    /// Run a full stop-the-world tri-color GC cycle.
    pub fn collect(&mut self) {
        println!("\n=== GC: Starting stop-the-world collection ===");
        self.stats.collections_run += 1;

        // Phase 1: Reset all objects to white
        self.reset_to_white();

        // Phase 2: Mark roots gray
        let root_ids: Vec<ObjectId> = self.roots.iter().copied().collect();
        let mut gray: VecDeque<ObjectId> = VecDeque::new();
        for id in root_ids {
            if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get_mut(&id) {
                if obj.color == Color::White {
                    obj.color = Color::Gray;
                    gray.push_back(id);
                    println!("  Mark root {} Gray", id);
                }
            }
        }

        // Phase 3: Process gray objects until none remain
        self.drain_gray_worklist_stw(&mut gray);

        // Phase 4: Sweep — collect all remaining white objects
        self.sweep();

        println!("=== GC: Collection complete. Stats: {} ===\n", self.stats);
    }

    fn reset_to_white(&mut self) {
        for obj in self.heap.values_mut() {
            obj.color = Color::White;
        }
    }

    fn drain_gray_worklist_stw(&mut self, gray: &mut VecDeque<ObjectId>) {
        while let Some(id) = gray.pop_front() {
            // Collect references first to avoid borrow conflict
            let refs: Vec<ObjectId> = self
                .heap
                .get(&id)
                .map(|o| o.references())
                .unwrap_or_default();

            // Shade children gray
            for child_id in refs {
                if let Some(child) = self.heap.get_mut(&child_id) {
                    if child.color == Color::White {
                        child.color = Color::Gray;
                        gray.push_back(child_id);
                        println!("  Mark {} Gray (child of {})", child_id, id);
                    }
                }
            }

            // Mark self black
            if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get_mut(&id) {
                obj.color = Color::Black;
                println!("  Mark {} Black", id);
            }
        }
    }

    fn sweep(&mut self) {
        let white_ids: Vec<ObjectId> = self
            .heap
            .values()
            .filter(|o| o.color == Color::White)
            .map(|o| o.id)
            .collect();

        let collected = white_ids.len();
        let survived = self.heap.len() - collected;

        for id in &white_ids {
            println!("  Sweep: collecting unreachable object {}", id);
            self.heap.remove(id);
            // Also remove from roots in case of dangling root
            self.roots.remove(id);
        }

        self.stats.objects_collected += collected;
        self.stats.objects_survived += survived;
        println!(
            "  Sweep done: {} collected, {} survived",
            collected, survived
        );
    }

    // ----------------------------------------------------------
    // Incremental collection
    // ----------------------------------------------------------

    /// Begin an incremental GC cycle (marks roots gray, returns immediately).
    pub fn incremental_start(&mut self) {
        if self.incremental_active {
            println!("GC: incremental cycle already active");
            return;
        }
        println!("\n=== GC: Starting incremental cycle ===");
        self.stats.collections_run += 1;
        self.incremental_active = true;

        // Reset all objects to white
        self.reset_to_white();
        self.gray_worklist.clear();

        // Mark roots gray
        let root_ids: Vec<ObjectId> = self.roots.iter().copied().collect();
        for id in root_ids {
            if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get_mut(&id) {
                if obj.color == Color::White {
                    obj.color = Color::Gray;
                    self.gray_worklist.push_back(id);
                    println!("  Incremental: root {} shaded Gray", id);
                }
            }
        }
    }

    /// Process up to `steps` gray objects.  Returns `true` if the marking
    /// phase is complete (gray worklist is empty).
    pub fn incremental_step(&mut self, steps: usize) -> bool {
        for _ in 0..steps {
            let id = match self.gray_worklist.pop_front() {
                Some(id) => id,
                None => return true,
            };

            let refs: Vec<ObjectId> = self
                .heap
                .get(&id)
                .map(|o| o.references())
                .unwrap_or_default();

            for child_id in refs {
                if let Some(child) = self.heap.get_mut(&child_id) {
                    if child.color == Color::White {
                        child.color = Color::Gray;
                        self.gray_worklist.push_back(child_id);
                        println!("  Incremental step: {} -> {} shaded Gray", id, child_id);
                    }
                }
            }

            if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get_mut(&id) {
                obj.color = Color::Black;
                println!("  Incremental step: {} -> Black", id);
            }
        }
        self.gray_worklist.is_empty()
    }

    /// Finish the incremental cycle: sweep white objects.
    /// Must be called after `incremental_step` returns `true`.
    pub fn incremental_finish(&mut self) {
        if !self.incremental_active {
            println!("GC: no active incremental cycle");
            return;
        }
        if !self.gray_worklist.is_empty() {
            println!("GC: warning — gray worklist not empty, forcing drain");
            let done = self.incremental_step(usize::MAX);
            assert!(done);
        }
        println!("  Incremental: sweeping...");
        self.sweep();
        self.incremental_active = false;
        println!("=== GC: Incremental cycle complete. Stats: {} ===\n", self.stats);
    }

    // ----------------------------------------------------------
    // Inspection helpers
    // ----------------------------------------------------------

    pub fn heap_size(&self) -> usize {
        self.heap.len()
    }

    pub fn get_object(&self, id: ObjectId) -> Option<&HeapObject> {
        self.heap.get(&id)
    }

    pub fn print_heap(&self) {
        println!("--- Heap ({} objects) ---", self.heap.len());
        let mut ids: Vec<ObjectId> = self.heap.keys().copied().collect();
        ids.sort_by_key(|id| id.0);
        for id in ids {
            if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get(&id) {
                let is_root = self.roots.contains(&obj.id);
                println!("  {} {}{}", obj, if is_root { "[ROOT]" } else { "" }, "");
            }
        }
        println!("------------------------");
    }

    pub fn print_colors(&self) {
        let mut ids: Vec<ObjectId> = self.heap.keys().copied().collect();
        ids.sort_by_key(|id| id.0);
        println!("Colors:");
        for id in ids {
            if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get(&id) {
                println!("  {} -> {}", obj.id, obj.color);
            }
        }
    }
}

impl Default for TriColorGc {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self::new()
    }
}

