## Key Design Decisions

| Feature | Choice | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| **Backing store** | `Vec<T>` | Contiguous memory, amortized O(1) push/pop |
| **Error handling** | `Result<T, StackError>` | Explicit, composable, no panics |
| **Generics** | `Stack<T>` | Works with any type |
| **Capacity** | `Option<usize>` | Supports both bounded and unbounded stacks |

## Complexity

| Operation | Time | Space |
|---|---|---|
| `push` | O(1) amortized | O(1) |
| `pop` | O(1) | O(1) |
| `peek` | O(1) | O(1) |
| `size` | O(1) | O(1) |
| `to_vec` | O(n) | O(n) |

# Palindrome Checker in Rust

## Implementation

```rust
fn is_palindrome(s: &str) -> bool {
    let chars: Vec<char> = s.chars().collect();
    let len = chars.len();

    for i in 0..len / 2 {
        if chars[i] != chars[len - 1 - i] {
            return false;
        }
    }

    true
}

/// Case-insensitive palindrome check that ignores non-alphanumeric characters
fn is_palindrome_relaxed(s: &str) -> bool {
    let filtered: Vec<char> = s
        .chars()
        .filter(|c| c.is_alphanumeric())
        .map(|c| c.to_lowercase().next().unwrap())
        .collect();

    let len = filtered.len();

    for i in 0..len / 2 {
        if filtered[i] != filtered[len - 1 - i] {
            return false;
        }
    }

    true
}

fn main() {
    // Strict palindrome tests
    let test_cases = vec![
        ("racecar", true),
        ("hello", false),
        ("madam", true),
        ("", true),
        ("a", true),
        ("ab", false),
        ("aba", true),
        ("abba", true),
        ("abcba", true),
    ];

    println!("=== Strict Palindrome Check ===");
    for (input, expected) in &test_cases {
        let result = is_palindrome(input);
        let status = if result == *expected { "✓" } else { "✗" };
        println!("{} \"{}\" => {}", status, input, result);
    }

    // Relaxed palindrome tests (ignores spaces, punctuation, case)
    let relaxed_cases = vec![
        ("A man a plan a canal Panama", true),
        ("Was it a car or a cat I saw", true),
        ("No lemon, no melon", true),
        ("Hello, World!", false),
        ("Never odd or even", true),
    ];

    println!("\n=== Relaxed Palindrome Check (case-insensitive, alphanumeric only) ===");
    for (input, expected) in &relaxed_cases {
        let result = is_palindrome_relaxed(input);
        let status = if result == *expected { "✓" } else { "✗" };
        println!("{} \"{}\" => {}", status, input, result);
    }
}

