## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| `f64` for token count | Enables fractional accumulation during refill so tokens aren't lost to integer rounding |
| `Arc<Mutex<BucketState>>` | Safe shared ownership across threads with minimal overhead |
| Lazy refill on access | Avoids background threads; tokens are calculated on demand from elapsed time |
| Two error variants | Distinguishes permanently-impossible requests from temporarily-limited ones |
| Builder pattern | Ergonomic construction without positional argument confusion |

## How It Works

```
Capacity:  [████████████████████] 20 tokens (max burst)
Refill:    +2 tokens/second

t=0s  consume(20) → [                    ] 0 tokens
t=1s  refill      → [████                ] 2 tokens
t=5s  refill      → [████████████████████] 10 tokens (capped)
```

1. **Refill** – On every operation, compute `elapsed × rate` and add tokens (capped at capacity)
2. **Consume** – If `tokens >= requested`, deduct and allow; otherwise return `RateLimited` with precise `retry_after`
3. **Blocking** – `consume()` calls `try_consume()` in a loop, sleeping for exactly the calculated `retry_after` duration

# Bounded Blocking Queue in Rust

## Overview

A bounded blocking queue that:
- **Blocks producers** when the queue is full
- **Blocks consumers** when the queue is empty
- Is **thread-safe** with multiple producers/consumers
- Uses `Mutex` + `Condvar` (the classic monitor pattern)

## Implementation

```rust
use std::collections::VecDeque;
use std::sync::{Arc, Condvar, Mutex};
use std::time::Duration;

/// Error types for the bounded blocking queue.
#[derive(Debug, PartialEq)]
pub enum QueueError {
    /// The queue has been closed/disconnected.
    Disconnected,
    /// A timed operation exceeded its deadline.
    Timeout,
}

impl std::fmt::Display for QueueError {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut std::fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> std::fmt::Result {
        match self {
            QueueError::Disconnected => write!(f, "Queue is disconnected"),
            QueueError::Timeout => write!(f, "Operation timed out"),
        }
    }
}

impl std::error::Error for QueueError {}

// ─── Internal state ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

struct Inner<T> {
    buf: VecDeque<T>,
    capacity: usize,
    closed: bool,
}

impl<T> Inner<T> {
    fn new(capacity: usize) -> Self {
        Self {
            buf: VecDeque::with_capacity(capacity),
            capacity,
            closed: false,
        }
    }

    fn is_full(&self) -> bool {
        self.buf.len() >= self.capacity
    }

    fn is_empty(&self) -> bool {
        self.buf.is_empty()
    }
}

// ─── Shared core ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

struct Shared<T> {
    inner: Mutex<Inner<T>>,
    not_full: Condvar,  // signalled when an item is removed
    not_empty: Condvar, // signalled when an item is added
}

// ─── Public handle (cheaply cloneable) ───────────────────────────────────────

/// A bounded, blocking, multi-producer / multi-consumer queue.
///
/// Clone the handle to share it across threads; all clones refer to the
/// same underlying queue.
pub struct BoundedBlockingQueue<T> {
    shared: Arc<Shared<T>>,
}

impl<T> Clone for BoundedBlockingQueue<T> {
    fn clone(&self) -> Self {
        Self {
            shared: Arc::clone(&self.shared),
        }
    }
}

impl<T> BoundedBlockingQueue<T> {
    // ── Construction ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    /// Creates a new queue that holds at most `capacity` items.
    ///
    /// # Panics
    /// Panics if `capacity == 0`.
    pub fn new(capacity: usize) -> Self {
        assert!(capacity > 0, "capacity must be greater than zero");
        Self {
            shared: Arc::new(Shared {
                inner: Mutex::new(Inner::new(capacity)),
                not_full: Condvar::new(),
                not_empty: Condvar::new(),
            }),
        }
    }

    // ── Producers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    /// Pushes `item` into the queue, **blocking** until space is available.
    ///
    /// Returns `Err(Disconnected)` if the queue has been closed.
    pub fn push(&self, item: T) -> Result<(), QueueError> {
        let mut guard = self.shared.inner.lock().unwrap();

        // Wait until there is space or the queue is closed.
        loop {
            if guard.closed {
                return Err(QueueError::Disconnected);
            }
            if !guard.is_full() {
                break;
            }
            guard = self.shared.not_full.wait(guard).unwrap();
        }

        guard.buf.push_back(item);
        drop(guard);

        // Wake one waiting consumer.
        self.shared.not_empty.notify_one();
        Ok(())
    }

    /// Tries to push `item` without blocking.
    ///
    /// Returns `Ok(())` on success, or the item back inside `Err` if the
    /// queue is full or closed.
    pub fn try_push(&self, item: T) -> Result<(), (T, QueueError)> {
        let mut guard = self.shared.inner.lock().unwrap();

        if guard.closed {
            return Err((item, QueueError::Disconnected));
        }
        if guard.is_full() {
            return Err((item, QueueError::Timeout)); // repurposed as "would block"
        }

        guard.buf.push_back(item);
        drop(guard);

        self.shared.not_empty.notify_one();
        Ok(())
    }

    /// Pushes `item`, waiting **at most** `timeout` for space to appear.
    pub fn push_timeout(&self, item: T, timeout: Duration) -> Result<(), (T, QueueError)> {
        let mut guard = self.shared.inner.lock().unwrap();

        loop {
            if guard.closed {
                return Err((item, QueueError::Disconnected));
            }
            if !guard.is_full() {
                break;
            }
            let (g, result) = self
                .shared
                .not_full
                .wait_timeout(guard, timeout)
                .unwrap();
            guard = g;
            if result.timed_out() {
                return Err((item, QueueError::Timeout));
            }
        }

        guard.buf.push_back(item);
        drop(guard);

        self.shared.not_empty.notify_one();
        Ok(())
    }

    // ── Consumers ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    /// Removes and returns the front item, **blocking** until one is available.
    ///
    /// Returns `Err(Disconnected)` only when the queue is *both* closed *and*
    /// empty (i.e. all remaining items have been drained).
    pub fn pop(&self) -> Result<T, QueueError> {
        let mut guard = self.shared.inner.lock().unwrap();

        loop {
            if let Some(item) = guard.buf.pop_front() {
                drop(guard);
                self.shared.not_full.notify_one();
                return Ok(item);
            }
            if guard.closed {
                return Err(QueueError::Disconnected);
            }
            guard = self.shared.not_empty.wait(guard).unwrap();
        }
    }

    /// Tries to pop without blocking.
    pub fn try_pop(&self) -> Result<T, QueueError> {
        let mut guard = self.shared.inner.lock().unwrap();

        if let Some(item) = guard.buf.pop_front() {
            drop(guard);
            self.shared.not_full.notify_one();
            return Ok(item);
        }
        if guard.closed {
            Err(QueueError::Disconnected)
        } else {
            Err(QueueError::Timeout) // "would block"
        }
    }

    /// Pops an item, waiting **at most** `timeout`.
    pub fn pop_timeout(&self, timeout: Duration) -> Result<T, QueueError> {
        let mut guard = self.shared.inner.lock().unwrap();

        loop {
            if let Some(item) = guard.buf.pop_front() {
                drop(guard);
                self.shared.not_full.notify_one();
                return Ok(item);
            }
            if guard.closed {
                return Err(QueueError::Disconnected);
            }
            let (g, result) = self
                .shared
                .not_empty
                .wait_timeout(guard, timeout)
                .unwrap();
            guard = g;
            if result.timed_out() {
                return Err(QueueError::Timeout);
            }
        }
    }

    // ── Lifecycle ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    /// Closes the queue.  
    /// Blocked producers/consumers are woken and will receive
    /// `Err(Disconnected)` once the queue is drained.
    pub fn close(&self) {
        let mut guard = self.shared.inner.lock().unwrap();
        guard.closed = true;
        drop(guard);
        // Wake everyone so they can observe the closed flag.
        self.shared.not_full.notify_all();
        self.shared.not_empty.notify_all();
    }

    // ── Inspection ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    /// Current number of items in the queue.
    pub fn len(&self) -> usize {
        self.shared.inner.lock().unwrap().buf.len()
    }

    pub fn is_empty(&self) -> bool {
        self.len() == 0
    }

    pub fn is_full(&self) -> bool {
        let guard = self.shared.inner.lock().unwrap();
        guard.is_full()
    }

    pub fn capacity(&self) -> usize {
        self.shared.inner.lock().unwrap().capacity
    }

    pub fn is_closed(&self) -> bool {
        self.shared.inner.lock().unwrap().closed
    }
}

