## How It Works

### Architecture

```
Pattern string
     │
     ▼
┌─────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────────┐
│  Parser │────▶│ AST: Vec<Vec<Node>>          │
└─────────┘     │  Node::Token(Token, Quant)   │
                │  Node::Group(branches, Quant)│
                └──────────────┬───────────────┘
                               │
                               ▼
                    ┌──────────────────┐
                    │ match_nodes()    │◀── recursive backtracking
                    └──────────────────┘
```

### Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| Recursive descent parser | Simple and directly mirrors grammar structure |
| Greedy matching with backtracking | Correct semantics for `*`, `+`, `?` |
| `Vec<char>` for matching | Correct Unicode char-by-char indexing |
| Alternation as `Vec<Vec<Node>>` | Natural representation for `\|` and `(a\|b)` |
| No captures | Keeps the implementation focused and simple |

### Running

```bash
cargo run      # runs main() with examples
cargo test     # runs all 30+ unit tests
```

# Longest Common Subsequence in Rust

## Implementation

```rust
fn longest_common_subsequence(s1: &str, s2: &str) -> String {
    let chars1: Vec<char> = s1.chars().collect();
    let chars2: Vec<char> = s2.chars().collect();
    let m = chars1.len();
    let n = chars2.len();

    // Build the DP table
    // dp[i][j] = length of LCS of chars1[..i] and chars2[..j]
    let mut dp = vec![vec![0usize; n + 1]; m + 1];

    for i in 1..=m {
        for j in 1..=n {
            if chars1[i - 1] == chars2[j - 1] {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1;
            } else {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j].max(dp[i][j - 1]);
            }
        }
    }

    // Backtrack to find the actual LCS string
    let mut lcs = Vec::new();
    let mut i = m;
    let mut j = n;

    while i > 0 && j > 0 {
        if chars1[i - 1] == chars2[j - 1] {
            lcs.push(chars1[i - 1]);
            i -= 1;
            j -= 1;
        } else if dp[i - 1][j] > dp[i][j - 1] {
            i -= 1;
        } else {
            j -= 1;
        }
    }

    lcs.iter().rev().collect()
}

fn lcs_length(s1: &str, s2: &str) -> usize {
    let chars1: Vec<char> = s1.chars().collect();
    let chars2: Vec<char> = s2.chars().collect();
    let m = chars1.len();
    let n = chars2.len();

    // Space-optimized version using only two rows
    let mut prev = vec![0usize; n + 1];
    let mut curr = vec![0usize; n + 1];

    for i in 1..=m {
        for j in 1..=n {
            if chars1[i - 1] == chars2[j - 1] {
                curr[j] = prev[j - 1] + 1;
            } else {
                curr[j] = prev[j].max(curr[j - 1]);
            }
        }
        std::mem::swap(&mut prev, &mut curr);
        curr.iter_mut().for_each(|x| *x = 0);
    }

    prev[n]
}

fn print_dp_table(s1: &str, s2: &str) {
    let chars1: Vec<char> = s1.chars().collect();
    let chars2: Vec<char> = s2.chars().collect();
    let m = chars1.len();
    let n = chars2.len();

    let mut dp = vec![vec![0usize; n + 1]; m + 1];

    for i in 1..=m {
        for j in 1..=n {
            if chars1[i - 1] == chars2[j - 1] {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1;
            } else {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j].max(dp[i][j - 1]);
            }
        }
    }

    // Print header
    print!("      ");
    for c in &chars2 {
        print!(" {:^3}", c);
    }
    println!();
    print!("   ");
    for _ in 0..=n {
        print!("{:^4}", "---");
    }
    println!();

    // Print rows
    for i in 0..=m {
        if i == 0 {
            print!("   |");
        } else {
            print!(" {} |", chars1[i - 1]);
        }
        for j in 0..=n {
            print!("{:^4}", dp[i][j]);
        }
        println!();
    }
}

fn main() {
    println!("=== Longest Common Subsequence ===\n");

    let test_cases = vec![
        ("ABCBDAB", "BDCABA"),
        ("AGGTAB", "GXTXAYB"),
        ("ABCDEF", "ABCDEF"),
        ("ABCDEF", "FEDCBA"),
        ("", "HELLO"),
