## Key Design Decisions

| Aspect | Choice | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Storage | `Vec<K>`, `Vec<V>`, `Vec<BTreeNode>` | Cache-friendly, dynamic sizing |
| Ownership | Node owns children | Clean Rust ownership, avoids unsafe |
| Splitting | Proactive (top-down) | Avoids backtracking; single pass down |
| Deletion | Case-based (CLRS §18.3) | Correct handling of underflow |
| Key type | Generic `K: Ord + Clone` | Works with any comparable type |

## Algorithm Complexity

| Operation | Time | Space |
|---|---|---|
| Search | O(log n) | O(h) stack |
| Insert | O(log n) | O(h) stack |
| Delete | O(log n) | O(h) stack |
| Traverse | O(n) | O(n) |

Where `h = O(log_t n)` is the tree height and `t` is the minimum degree.

