## Key Design Decisions

### Persistence via `Arc<Node>`

```
          t1                    t2 (after insert "fig")
          │                     │
      [black]               [black]  ← new node
      /       \             /     \
  [apple]  [cherry]    shared    [fig]  ← new node
     ↑          ↑        subtrees
  shared      shared     from t1
  with t2     with t2
```

`Arc` provides reference-counted, immutable sharing. Only nodes on the path from root to the modified node are copied — `O(log n)` new allocations per operation.

### Algorithms Used

| Operation | Algorithm | Complexity |
|-----------|-----------|------------|
| `get`     | Iterative BST search | O(log n) |
| `insert`  | Okasaki (1999) functional insertion + 4-case `balance` | O(log n) |
| `delete`  | Kahrs (2001) / Germane & Might deletion with `balance_left`/`balance_right` | O(log n) |

### The Four `balance` Patterns

```
         z                    y
        / \                 /   \
       y   d     →        x     z
      / \                / \   / \
     x   c              a  b  c   d
    / \
   a   b

(and the mirror image, plus right-left and right-right variants)
```

Every pattern detects a **double-red** violation and performs a single rotation + recolor.

# Tri-Color Garbage Collector in Rust

## Overview

The tri-color marking algorithm uses three sets:
- **White**: Not yet visited (candidates for collection)
- **Gray**: Discovered but children not yet scanned
- **Black**: Fully scanned (kept alive)

```rust
use std::collections::{HashMap, HashSet, VecDeque};
use std::fmt;

// ============================================================
// Core Types
// ============================================================

/// Unique identifier for a garbage-collected object
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
pub struct GcId(usize);

impl fmt::Display for GcId {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        write!(f, "GcId({})", self.0)
    }
}

/// Color of an object in the tri-color marking scheme
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub enum Color {
    /// Not yet discovered — candidate for collection
    White,
    /// Discovered but children not yet fully scanned
    Gray,
    /// Fully scanned — definitely reachable
    Black,
}

impl fmt::Display for Color {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        match self {
            Color::White => write!(f, "White"),
            Color::Gray  => write!(f, "Gray"),
            Color::Black => write!(f, "Black"),
        }
    }
}

// ============================================================
// Value & Object
// ============================================================

/// A value that can live on the GC heap
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub enum Value {
    Null,
    Int(i64),
    Float(f64),
    Bool(bool),
    Str(String),
    /// Reference to another GC-managed object
    Ref(GcId),
    /// Heterogeneous list of values (may contain Ref variants)
    List(Vec<Value>),
}

impl fmt::Display for Value {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        match self {
            Value::Null        => write!(f, "null"),
            Value::Int(n)      => write!(f, "{n}"),
            Value::Float(x)    => write!(f, "{x}"),
            Value::Bool(b)     => write!(f, "{b}"),
            Value::Str(s)      => write!(f, "{s:?}"),
            Value::Ref(id)     => write!(f, "ref:{id}"),
            Value::List(items) => {
                write!(f, "[")?;
                for (i, v) in items.iter().enumerate() {
                    if i > 0 { write!(f, ", ")?; }
                    write!(f, "{v}")?;
                }
                write!(f, "]")
            }
        }
    }
}

impl Value {
    /// Collect all GcIds directly referenced by this value
    fn references(&self) -> Vec<GcId> {
        match self {
            Value::Ref(id)     => vec![*id],
            Value::List(items) => items.iter().flat_map(|v| v.references()).collect(),
            _                  => vec![],
        }
    }
}

/// A heap-allocated object tracked by the GC
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct GcObject {
    pub id:     GcId,
    pub name:   String,          // human-readable label
    pub color:  Color,
    pub fields: HashMap<String, Value>,
}

impl GcObject {
    fn new(id: GcId, name: impl Into<String>) -> Self {
        Self {
            id,
            name:   name.into(),
            color:  Color::White,
            fields: HashMap::new(),
        }
    }

    /// All GcIds this object points to (across all fields)
    fn references(&self) -> Vec<GcId> {
        self.fields.values().flat_map(|v| v.references()).collect()
    }
}

impl fmt::Display for GcObject {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        write!(f, "[{}] {} ({}) {{", self.id, self.name, self.color)?;
        let mut first = true;
        for (k, v) in &self.fields {
            if !first { write!(f, ", ")?; }
            write!(f, "{k}: {v}")?;
            first = false;
        }
        write!(f, "}}")
    }
}

// ============================================================
// Write Barrier
// ============================================================

/// Records a pointer write that happened during an incremental GC cycle.
/// The write barrier ensures the tri-color invariant is maintained:
/// a Black object must never point to a White object.
#[derive(Debug)]
struct WriteBarrierEntry {
    /// Object that was modified
    object_id: GcId,
}

// ============================================================
// Garbage Collector
// ============================================================

/// Statistics collected during a GC cycle
#[derive(Debug, Default, Clone)]
pub struct GcStats {
    pub cycles:         usize,
    pub objects_marked: usize,
    pub objects_freed:  usize,
    pub objects_kept:   usize,
    pub total_allocated: usize,
}

impl fmt::Display for GcStats {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        writeln!(f, "GC Statistics:")?;
        writeln!(f, "  Cycles run       : {}", self.cycles)?;
        writeln!(f, "  Total allocated  : {}", self.total_allocated)?;
        writeln!(f, "  Objects marked   : {}", self.objects_marked)?;
        writeln!(f, "  Objects freed    : {}", self.objects_freed)?;
        write!(  f, "  Objects kept     : {}", self.objects_kept)
    }
}

/// Tri-color incremental garbage collector
pub struct GarbageCollector {
    /// All live heap objects
    heap:       HashMap<GcId, GcObject>,
    /// Root set — objects the mutator directly holds references to
    roots:      HashSet<GcId>,
    /// Gray worklist (BFS queue)
    gray_queue: VecDeque<GcId>,
    /// Write-barrier log (pointer stores during incremental marking)
    write_log:  Vec<WriteBarrierEntry>,
    /// Next id to assign
    next_id:    usize,
    /// Accumulated statistics
    pub stats:  GcStats,
    /// Whether an incremental mark phase is in progress
    marking:    bool,
}

impl GarbageCollector {
    // --------------------------------------------------------
    // Construction
    // --------------------------------------------------------

    pub fn new() -> Self {
        Self {
            heap:       HashMap::new(),
            roots:      HashSet::new(),
            gray_queue: VecDeque::new(),
            write_log:  Vec::new(),
            next_id:    0,
            stats:      GcStats::default(),
            marking:    false,
        }
    }

    // --------------------------------------------------------
    // Allocation
    // --------------------------------------------------------

    /// Allocate a new object on the GC heap and return its id
    pub fn allocate(&mut self, name: impl Into<String>) -> GcId {
        let id  = GcId(self.next_id);
        self.next_id += 1;
        let obj = GcObject::new(id, name);
        self.heap.insert(id, obj);
        self.stats.total_allocated += 1;

        // If a mark phase is in progress the new object starts Gray
        // (allocation barrier) so it is never swept before being examined.
        if self.marking {
            if let Some(o) = self.heap.get_mut(&id) {
                o.color = Color::Gray;
            }
            self.gray_queue.push_back(id);
        }

        id
    }

    // --------------------------------------------------------
    // Root management
    // --------------------------------------------------------

    pub fn add_root(&mut self, id: GcId) {
        self.roots.insert(id);
    }

    pub fn remove_root(&mut self, id: GcId) {
        self.roots.remove(&id);
    }

    // --------------------------------------------------------
    // Mutator helpers (field access with write barrier)
    // --------------------------------------------------------

    /// Set a field on an object; invokes write barrier if needed
    pub fn set_field(&mut self, obj_id: GcId, field: impl Into<String>, value: Value) {
        // Write barrier: if the mutating object is Black and we are in an
        // active mark phase, re-gray it so its new outgoing edges are scanned.
        if self.marking {
            if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get(&obj_id) {
                if obj.color == Color::Black {
                    self.write_log.push(WriteBarrierEntry { object_id: obj_id });
                }
            }
        }
        if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get_mut(&obj_id) {
            obj.fields.insert(field.into(), value);
        }
    }

    /// Read a field value (returns a clone)
    pub fn get_field(&self, obj_id: GcId, field: &str) -> Option<Value> {
        self.heap.get(&obj_id)?.fields.get(field).cloned()
    }

    // --------------------------------------------------------
    // Full stop-the-world collection
    // --------------------------------------------------------

    /// Run a complete stop-the-world tri-color collection cycle.
    pub fn collect(&mut self) {
        println!("\n=== GC cycle {} (stop-the-world) ===", self.stats.cycles + 1);

        self.phase_reset();
        self.phase_mark_roots();
        // Drain the entire gray queue
        while !self.gray_queue.is_empty() {
            self.step_mark(usize::MAX);
        }
        self.phase_sweep();

        self.marking = false;
        self.stats.cycles += 1;
    }

    // --------------------------------------------------------
    // Incremental collection (call step() repeatedly)
    // --------------------------------------------------------

    /// Start an incremental GC cycle (reset + mark roots).
    pub fn incremental_start(&mut self) {
        println!("\n=== GC cycle {} (incremental start) ===", self.stats.cycles + 1);
        self.phase_reset();
        self.phase_mark_roots();
    }

    /// Perform up to `work_units` marking steps.
    /// Returns `true` when the mark phase is complete.
    pub fn incremental_step(&mut self, work_units: usize) -> bool {
        // First, drain the write-barrier log
        self.drain_write_log();

        if self.gray_queue.is_empty() {
            return true; // marking done
        }
        self.step_mark(work_units);

        // Re-drain any new write-barrier entries produced during this step
        self.drain_write_log();

        self.gray_queue.is_empty()
    }

    /// Finish the incremental cycle (sweep phase).
    /// Must only be called after `incremental_step` returns `true`.
    pub fn incremental_finish(&mut self) {
        self.phase_sweep();
        self.marking = false;
        self.stats.cycles += 1;
        println!("=== GC cycle {} complete ===", self.stats.cycles);
    }

    // --------------------------------------------------------
    // Internal phases
    // --------------------------------------------------------

    /// Phase 0 – Reset all objects to White, clear gray queue
    fn phase_reset(&mut self) {
        for obj in self.heap.values_mut() {
            obj.color = Color::White;
        }
        self.gray_queue.clear();
        self.write_log.clear();
        self.marking = true;
    }

    /// Phase 1 – Mark roots Gray and enqueue them
    fn phase_mark_roots(&mut self) {
        for &root_id in &self.roots {
            if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get_mut(&root_id) {
                if obj.color == Color::White {
                    obj.color = Color::Gray;
                    self.gray_queue.push_back(root_id);
                }
            }
        }
        println!("  Roots marked gray: {:?}", self.roots);
    }

    /// Phase 2 – Process up to `limit` gray objects
    fn step_mark(&mut self, limit: usize) {
        let mut processed = 0;
        while processed < limit {
            let Some(id) = self.gray_queue.pop_front() else { break };

            // Collect references before mutating to satisfy the borrow checker
            let refs: Vec<GcId> = match self.heap.get(&id) {
                Some(obj) => obj.references(),
                None      => continue,
            };

            // Turn the gray object Black
            if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get_mut(&id) {
                obj.color = Color::Black;
            }

            // Turn all White children Gray and enqueue them
            for child_id in refs {
                if let Some(child) = self.heap.get_mut(&child_id) {
                    if child.color == Color::White {
                        child.color = Color::Gray;
                        self.gray_queue.push_back(child_id);
                    }
                }
            }

            self.stats.objects_marked += 1;
            processed += 1;
        }
    }

    /// Phase 3 – Sweep all White objects (unreachable → collect)
    fn phase_sweep(&mut self) {
        let dead: Vec<GcId> = self.heap.values()
            .filter(|obj| obj.color == Color::White)
            .map(|obj| obj.id)
            .collect();

        let kept = self.heap.len() - dead.len();

        for id in &dead {
            println!("  Collecting: {}", self.heap[id]);
            self.heap.remove(id);
            // Also ensure it's not a dangling root
            self.roots.remove(id);
        }

        self.stats.objects_freed += dead.len();
        self.stats.objects_kept  += kept;

        println!(
            "  Sweep: freed={}, kept={}",
            dead.len(), kept
        );
    }

    /// Drain write-barrier log: re-gray any Black objects that were mutated
    fn drain_write_log(&mut self) {
        let entries: Vec<_> = self.write_log.drain(..).collect();
        for entry in entries {
            if let Some(obj) = self.heap.get_mut(&entry.object_id) {
                if obj.color == Color::Black {
                    println!("  Write barrier: re-graying {}", obj.id);
                    obj.color = Color::Gray;
                    self.gray_queue.push_back(obj.id);
                }
            }
        }
    }

    // --------------------------------------------------------
    // Diagnostics
    // --------------------------------------------------------

    pub fn heap_size(&self) -> usize {
        self.heap.len()
    }

    pub fn print_heap(&self) {
        println!("--- Heap ({} objects) ---", self.heap.len());
        let mut ids: Vec<_> = self.heap.keys().collect();
        ids.sort_by_key(|id| id.0);
        for id in ids {
            println!("  {}", self.heap[id]);
        }
        println!("  Roots: {:?}", self.roots);
    }

    pub fn dump_colors(&self) {
        println!("--- Object colors ---");
        let mut ids: Vec<_> = self.heap.keys().collect();
        ids.sort_by_key(|id| id.0);
        for id in ids {
            let obj = &self.heap[id];
            println!("  {} => {}", obj.name, obj.color);
        }
    }
}

impl Default for GarbageCollector {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self::new()
    }
}

