## How It Works

### `is_palindrome` (basic)
| Step | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Collect chars | Convert `&str` to `Vec<char>` for O(1) indexed access |
| Two pointers | Start from both ends, move inward |
| Compare | Return `false` on first mismatch, `true` if pointers meet |

### `is_palindrome_alphanumeric` (real-world)
| Step | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Filter | Remove non-alphanumeric characters |
| Normalize | Convert to lowercase |
| Compare | Zip first half with reversed second half |

## Key Rust Concepts Used

- **`&str` vs `String`** — takes a string slice for flexibility
- **`chars()`** — correctly handles multi-byte Unicode characters instead of indexing bytes directly
- **Iterators** — `filter`, `map`, `zip`, `all` for clean, idiomatic code
- **Two-pointer technique** — O(n) time, O(n) space (for char collection)

