## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| `f64` for tokens | Allows fractional tokens and smooth refill math |
| Lazy refill | Tokens are only recalculated on access, not on a timer thread |
| `Arc<Mutex<T>>` | Standard interior mutability for thread-safe sharing |
| Start bucket full | Avoids penalizing new clients; bursts are intentional |
| `KeyedRateLimiter<K>` | Separate bucket per key — clients don't share quota |

## Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│           KeyedRateLimiter<K>           │  Per-key (IP, user, API key)
│  HashMap<K, RateLimiter>               │
└────────────────┬────────────────────────┘
                 │ contains many
┌────────────────▼────────────────────────┐
│             RateLimiter                 │  Thread-safe wrapper
│  Arc<Mutex<TokenBucket>>               │
└────────────────┬────────────────────────┘
                 │ wraps
┌────────────────▼────────────────────────┐
│            TokenBucket                  │  Core algorithm
│  capacity, tokens, refill_rate,        │
│  last_refill: Instant                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Usage Examples

```rust
