## How It Works

### Architecture

```
Pattern string
     │
     ▼
  Parser  →  AST (Vec<Node>)
                 │
                 ▼
  Matcher (recursive backtracking)
                 │
                 ▼
           Match result
```

### Key Design Decisions

| Concern | Approach |
|---|---|
| **Parsing** | Recursive descent with explicit alternation/sequence/atom layers |
| **AST** | `Node { atom, quantifier, greedy }` — clean separation of concerns |
| **Matching** | Backtracking via recursion over `nodes[idx..]` and `text[pos..]` |
| **Greedy vs Lazy** | Greedy collects all positions then tries longest-first; lazy tries shortest-first |
| **Groups/Alternation** | Matched recursively; transparent to the outer sequence |
| **Unicode** | Works on `Vec<char>`; byte offsets translated for string slices |

### Supported Syntax

| Syntax | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `abc` | Literal characters |
| `.` | Any character except newline |
| `*` `+` `?` | Greedy quantifiers |
| `*?` `+?` `??` | Lazy quantifiers |
| `^` `$` | Start/end anchors |
| `[a-z]` | Character class with ranges |
| `[^abc]` | Negated character class |
| `\d` `\D` | Digit / non-digit |
| `\w` `\W` | Word char / non-word char |
| `\s` `\S` | Whitespace / non-whitespace |
| `(...)` | Grouping |
| `a\|b` | Alternation |

# Longest Common Subsequence in Rust

## Implementation

```rust
fn longest_common_subsequence(s1: &str, s2: &str) -> String {
    let chars1: Vec<char> = s1.chars().collect();
    let chars2: Vec<char> = s2.chars().collect();
    let m = chars1.len();
    let n = chars2.len();

    // Build the DP table
    // dp[i][j] = length of LCS of chars1[0..i] and chars2[0..j]
    let mut dp = vec![vec![0usize; n + 1]; m + 1];

    for i in 1..=m {
        for j in 1..=n {
            if chars1[i - 1] == chars2[j - 1] {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1;
            } else {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j].max(dp[i][j - 1]);
            }
        }
    }

    // Backtrack to find the actual LCS string
    let mut lcs = Vec::new();
    let mut i = m;
    let mut j = n;

    while i > 0 && j > 0 {
        if chars1[i - 1] == chars2[j - 1] {
            lcs.push(chars1[i - 1]);
            i -= 1;
            j -= 1;
        } else if dp[i - 1][j] > dp[i][j - 1] {
            i -= 1;
        } else {
            j -= 1;
        }
    }

    lcs.reverse();
    lcs.iter().collect()
}

fn lcs_length(s1: &str, s2: &str) -> usize {
    let chars1: Vec<char> = s1.chars().collect();
    let chars2: Vec<char> = s2.chars().collect();
    let m = chars1.len();
    let n = chars2.len();

    // Space-optimized version using only two rows
    let mut prev = vec![0usize; n + 1];
    let mut curr = vec![0usize; n + 1];

    for i in 1..=m {
        for j in 1..=n {
            if chars1[i - 1] == chars2[j - 1] {
                curr[j] = prev[j - 1] + 1;
            } else {
                curr[j] = prev[j].max(curr[j - 1]);
            }
        }
        std::mem::swap(&mut prev, &mut curr);
        curr.fill(0);
    }

    prev[n]
}

fn all_lcs(s1: &str, s2: &str) -> Vec<String> {
    let chars1: Vec<char> = s1.chars().collect();
    let chars2: Vec<char> = s2.chars().collect();
    let m = chars1.len();
    let n = chars2.len();

    let mut dp = vec![vec![0usize; n + 1]; m + 1];

    for i in 1..=m {
        for j in 1..=n {
            if chars1[i - 1] == chars2[j - 1] {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1;
            } else {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j].max(dp[i][j - 1]);
            }
        }
    }

    // Recursively backtrack all possible LCS strings
    fn backtrack(
        dp: &Vec<Vec<usize>>,
        chars1: &[char],
        chars2: &[char],
        i: usize,
        j: usize,
    ) -> Vec<String> {
        if i == 0 || j == 0 {
            return vec![String::new()];
        }

        if chars1[i - 1] == chars2[j - 1] {
            backtrack(dp, chars1, chars2, i - 1, j - 1)
                .into_iter()
                .map(|mut s| {
                    s.push(chars1[i - 1]);
                    s
                })
                .collect()
        } else {
            let mut results = Vec::new();

            if dp[i - 1][j] >= dp[i][j - 1] {
                results.extend(backtrack(dp, chars1, chars2, i - 1, j));
            }
            if dp[i][j - 1] >= dp[i - 1][j] {
                results.extend(backtrack(dp, chars1, chars2, i, j - 1));
            }

            // Deduplicate
            results.sort();
            results.dedup();
            results
        }
    }

    backtrack(&dp, &chars1, &chars2, m, n)
}

fn print_dp_table(s1: &str, s2: &str) {
    let chars1: Vec<char> = s1.chars().collect();
    let chars2: Vec<char> = s2.chars().collect();
    let m = chars1.len();
    let n = chars2.len();

    let mut dp = vec![vec![0usize; n + 1]; m + 1];

    for i in 1..=m {
        for j in 1..=n {
            if chars1[i - 1] == chars2[j - 1] {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j - 1] + 1;
            } else {
                dp[i][j] = dp[i - 1][j].max(dp[i][j - 1]);
            }
        }
    }

    // Print header
    print!("      ");
    for c in &chars2 {
        print!("  {}", c);
    }
    println!();
    print!("   ");
    for _ in 0..=n {
        print!("{:3}", 0);
    }
    println!();

